```
From:Jared Isaacman
Sent:Friday, July 19, 2019 1:49 PM
To:Bredimus, Jeffrey; 'Angela Bostock'
Cc:Isaacman, Taylor
Subject:Card Connect - Finalize July Projections

Jeff and Angela,

Please provide completed projections which incorporate the
adjustments below.

1.  Lower total revenue by $4-5M to reflect more of a
    straight-line
    revenue recognition on the enterprise deals
    completed this year. The previous approach had those
    deals recognized almost entirely in 2019.

2.  Increase hardware costs to reflect the plan discussed to
    ship hardware to customers, where we would recover the
    cost over the contract term. We have committed on many
    occasions we can recover the cost of hardware through install
    fees, monthly fees or over the term of the contract. Hardware
    costs should at minimum be in line with last year at around
    $18-20M.

3.  Intercompany Royalty. The royalty at CardConnect is
    expected to be eliminated after the transaction closes. We
    have discussed this on many occasions. We simply must
    arrive at the same assumption and PWC should be providing
    CardConnect with a memo justifying the position. Taylor
    spent most of yesterday on this with PWC and it still is not
    resolved.

4.  All other revenue assumptions should match the plan as it
    was presented to the Board, which I will get you today.

```
